examples.en: She longed for him to return.
He longed to see her again.
He longed for the touch of her hand.
He longed to sprawl out on a bed.
She longed for the chance to speak to him in private.
He longed to lead his men on to victory.
I longed to be free of my family.
She longed to be freed of her responsibilities.
He longed for the fields of his youth.
He longed to join the upper social ranks.
All his life he longed to return to his motherland.
I longed to go nearer it, but the prohibition withheld me.
He longed for the flowers that were yet to show themselves.
He longed for the comfortable environment of his living room.
He longed in some vague way for something different.
She was tired of moving around and longed for a more settled existence.
She always longed to return to the quiet hamlet where she had been born.
After being awake for three days straight, he longed for the oblivion of sleep.
